    "body": "BufRead autocommands are not being run. Vim 8.2 works as expected.\r\n\r\n- `nvim --version`:\r\n ```\r\nNVIM v0.5.0-dev+a58c550\r\nBuild type: Release\r\nLuaJIT 2.1.0-beta3\r\nCompilation: /usr/bin/clang -U_FORTIFY_SOURCE -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=1 -DNDEBUG -Wall -Wextra -pedantic -Wno-unused-parameter -Wstrict-prototypes -std=gnu99 -Wshadow -Wconversion -Wmissing-prototypes -Wimplicit-fallthrough -Wvla -fstack-protector-strong -fno-common -fdiagnostics-color=auto -DINCLUDE_GENERATED_DECLARATIONS -D_GNU_SOURCE -DNVIM_MSGPACK_HAS_FLOAT32 -DNVIM_UNIBI_HAS_VAR_FROM -DMIN_LOG_LEVEL=3 -I/tmp/neovim-20201227-3289-9mymck/build/config -I/tmp/neovim-20201227-3289-9mymck/src -I/usr/local/include -I/tmp/neovim-20201227-3289-9mymck/deps-build/include -I/Library/Developer/CommandLineTools/SDKs/MacOSX10.14.sdk/usr/include -I/usr/local/opt/gettext/include -I/tmp/neovim-20201227-3289-9mymck/build/src/nvim/auto -I/tmp/neovim-20201227-3289-9mymck/build/include\r\nCompiled by kevin@My-MacBook-Pro.attlocal.net\r\n\r\nFeatures: +acl +iconv +tui\r\nSee \":help feature-compile\"\r\n\r\n   system vimrc file: \"$VIM/sysinit.vim\"\r\n  fall-back for $VIM: \"/usr/local/Cellar/neovim/HEAD-a58c550/share/nvim\"\r\n\r\nRun :checkhealth for more info\r\n ```\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: 8.2) behaves differently?:  **Yes** (well, with same `minimal_example.vim` below in place of DEFAULTS)\r\n- Operating system/version: macOS Mojave 10.14.6 (18G7016)\r\n- Terminal name/version: iTerm2 Build 3.4.3\r\n- `$TERM`: xterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Create a file called `minimal_example.vim` with the following contents:\r\n```\r\nautocmd BufRead * :echom 'Hello world'\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Create a example file to read by running `touch example.txt`\r\n\r\n3. Open this file using `nvim -u minimal_example.vim example.txt`\r\n\r\n4. Now type `:messages<Enter>`\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\nThere are no messages\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\nMessages lists `Hello world`\r\n\r\n",
